race.comment: SHADOWFAX (1) was well backed first-up but faded badly after leading in town. Drops in grade and gets the 3kg claim to sharpen him right up. Expecting a bounce and he's the one they'll be chasing. HASSLEFREE (2) found form on the dirt at Pooncarie and has a solid record over this trip. He's fit, firing, and deserves plenty of respect. AVANZO (8) didn't show last start but was eye-catching fresh at Balaklava. Third-up suits and she's got the turn of foot to feature. BROADWAY LANE (9) flopped as favourite last time. Light weight and early prep form suggest he's worth another look. LAVA LAD (6) hasn't fired fresh but knows how to win here and gets a familiar rider back on. Capable of featuring.
